article.description: — Chris Manon's 12 points helped Cornell defeat Lafayette 73-68 on Sunday.
article.headline: Manon scores 12, Cornell defeats Lafayette 73-68
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- — Chris Manon's 12 points helped Cornell defeat Lafayette 73-68 on Sunday. Manon had six rebounds for the Big Red (7-1). Nazir Williams scored 12 points and added five rebounds. Greg Dolan shot 5 for 11, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. It was the seventh straight win for the Big Red. Kyle Jenkins led the Leopards (1-8) in scoring, finishing with 17 points, eight rebounds and five assists. Leo O'Boyle added 14 points and four assists for Lafayette. In addition, T.J. Berger finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
